.TH BACKFILL_ARTIST_IDENTITY 1 "2026-03-18" "stophammer" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
backfill_artist_identity \- merge split canonical artists using strong evidence
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B backfill_artist_identity
[
.BI --db " PATH"
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B backfill_artist_identity
deterministically merges split canonical artists when strong staged source
evidence agrees across source IDs, publisher links, websites, or release
clusters.

Stored artist-identity overrides are honored during this backfill. A durable
do-not-merge override blocks the corresponding automatic merge, and a durable
merge override forces the selected target artist when the target still exists.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --db " PATH"
Path to the SQLite database. Defaults to
.BR ./stophammer.db .
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Run artist identity backfill:
.nf
cargo run --bin backfill_artist_identity -- --db ./stophammer.db
.fi
.TP
Review pending artist-identity items before running a broader repair pass:
.nf
cargo run --bin review_artist_identity -- --db ./stophammer.db --pending-reviews --limit 20
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR stophammer (1),
.BR backfill_canonical (1),
.BR review_artist_identity (1)
